DOCUMENT();

####################
# Load Macros
####################
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
  "contextIntegerFunctions.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

####################
# Header
####################
COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
TEXT(beginproblem());

####################
# PG Setup
####################
Context("IntegerFunctions");
Context("IntegerFunctions");
#Context()->texStrings;
@bank = ("seeded", "voodoo", "assess", "allele", "assesses");
$tag = random(0,4,1); #there are only 5 words in the bank (all that I could think of with only 3 distinct letters and interesting length; add more if possible

$word = $bank[$tag];
if ($tag ==0) 
{
$wlength = 6;
$letter = "s";
$spot = 2;
}
elsif ($tag ==1)
{
$wlength = 6;
$letter = "v";
$spot = 1;
}
elsif ( $tag == 2 )
{
$wlength = 6;
$letter = "a";
$spot = 1;
}
elsif ( $tag == 3) 
{
$wlength = 6;
$letter = "a";
$spot = 2;
}
elsif ( $tag == 4)
{
$wlength = 8;
$letter = "a";
$spot = 2;
}

$length = $wlength - 1; #count letters remaining after the first
$ans = Compute("C($length,$spot)");

####################
# Body
####################
BEGIN_PGML
How many anagrams are there of the word "[$word]" that start with the letter "[$letter]"?

[_____]{$ans}


END_PGML

####################
# Solution
####################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
After the first letter ([$letter]), we must rearrange the remaining [$length] letters. There are only two choices of letter now, so this is really just a bit-string question where one of the letters is 0, and the other letter is 1.  Thus there are [`{[$length] \choose [$spot]} = [$ans]`] anagrams starting with "[$letter]".


END_PGML_SOLUTION

####################
# End Problem
####################
ENDDOCUMENT();